# Media Query Syntax üìè

Media queries allow you to apply CSS styles only if a certain condition is true.

```css
@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  body {
    background-color: lightblue;
  }
}
```
If the browser window is 600px or smaller, the background color will be lightblue.

# Common Breakpoints üß±

Widths where the layout changes.

```css
/* Extra small devices (phones, 600px and down) */
@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {...}

/* Small devices (portrait tablets and large phones, 600px and up) */
@media only screen and (min-width: 600px) {...}

/* Medium devices (landscape tablets, 768px and up) */
@media only screen and (min-width: 768px) {...}

/* Large devices (laptops/desktops, 992px and up) */
@media only screen and (min-width: 992px) {...}

/* Extra large devices (large laptops and desktops, 1200px and up) */
@media only screen and (min-width: 1200px) {...}
```

# Mobile First Strategy üì≤

Design for mobile first, then scale up.

This means using `min-width` queries.

```css
/* Default styles for mobile */
.col { width: 100%; }

/* Tablet (768px+) */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .col { width: 50%; }
}

/* Desktop (1024px+) */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .col { width: 33.33%; }
}
```

# Orientation üß≠

You can distinct between portrait and landscape mode.

```css
@media only screen and (orientation: landscape) {
  body {
    background-color: lightblue;
  }
}
```

# Hiding Elements üôà

Sometimes you want to hide elements on smaller screens (like a large sidebar).

```css
/* Hide sidebar on screens smaller than 700px */
@media screen and (max-width: 700px) {
  .sidebar {
    display: none;
  }
}
```

# Responsive Typography üî†

Adjust text size for readability.

```css
font-size: 16px;

@media screen and (min-width: 800px) {
  div.content {
    font-size: 20px;
  }
}
```

Also consider using viewport units: `font-size: 3vw;` (3% of viewport width).

# Responsive Flexbox üßò

A common pattern: Row on desktop, Column on mobile.

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

@media (min-width: 600px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: row;
  }
}
```

# Advanced Media Features üïµÔ∏è

Modern CSS allows checking for more than width.

- `prefers-color-scheme: dark`: Check if user wants Dark Mode.
- `hover: hover`: Check if device has a cursor (mouse vs touch).

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body {
    background-color: black;
    color: white;
  }
}
```
